This application demonstrates the functionality of the biometric authentication cloud service OnePass provided by the STC-innovation Ltd.
In this application it’s possible to create your own biometrical password and go through the verification.
OnePass technology: touchless biometric authentication service 
OnePass is a bimodal biometric authentication service that stands on 3 main pillars:
1. Facial verification  is done at the very beginning. The whole process is similar to a selfie, during which the system analyzes distinctive facial features.
2. Voice verification is based on a dynamic password phrase that has to be read aloud from the screen. The passphrase is new every time, so there is no need to remember anything. Crucial element is not the password itself, but the identified voice pattern.
3. Liveness detection determines whether the person in front of the camera is authentic, not photographed or recorded. It analyzes recorded during the voice verification stage mimic expressions and makes the conclusion about whether the person in front of the camera is real, or recorded. This algorithm serves as protection against photo, video or audio usage by potential hackers.

As to security of the user data, it is stored in an encrypted form, so even if the database gets hacked or stolen, there is no way it can actually be used. It's impossible to reverse the voice and image synthesis and, luckily, OnePass only recognises live voice and dynamic image from the camera.
